    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3 id="toc_16">Set dns server for dnsmasq</h3>

<p>Use a separate conf file, the format is the same as resolv.conf.
<code>
resolv-file=/etc/resolv.masq.conf
</code>
Then after dnsmasq is started, set <code>127.0.0.1</code> in <code>/etc/resolv.conf</code>.</p>

<h3 id="toc_17">listening address with localhost</h3>
<div class="highlight"><pre><code class="text">listen-address=127.0.0.1
</code></pre>
</div>

<h3 id="toc_18">Use separate DNS for certain domains</h3>
<div class="highlight"><pre><code class="text">server=/www.google.com/8.8.8.8
</code></pre>
</div>

<h3 id="toc_19">Use regular expression for server</h3>
<div class="highlight"><pre><code class="text">server=/:.*google.*/8.8.8.8
</code></pre>
</div>
